I did a pass. The comment indentation is different from our conventions. Instead of 

```
    /// <summary>
    ///     Some comment
    /// </summary>
```

we usually have

```
    /// <summary>
    /// Some comment
    /// </summary>
```

@markusweimer @beysims @jwang98052 

I have incorporated RemoteManagerFactory with Writables also. Please have a look. If things are fine please merge.

Dhruv

This looks like an improvement to me, thanks! After testing, this can go in as-is.

However, on REEF-304, I think we can do better still. The code as is still has an an justified memory usage of O(#contexts), as we load the _same_ class hierarchy for the CLR for every context.

@jwang98052 @beysims: Do we actually modify the class hierarchy once loaded? If not, we probably should load it once, preferably in a Tang-managed object or via an external constructor.
